  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Recession, Poverty &amp; Sustainable Livelihoods in Bradford</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will research the impact of the recession on poverty in Bradford, West Yorkshire, and identify key local policy changes to enable communities to become more resilient in the future. We will work with the International Centre for Participation Studies (ICPS) at Bradford University, to recruit community researchers to carry out qualitative research with people in poverty and  verify this information with local communities. The research team will combine this information with a review of the external context to identify interventions that would strengthen people&apos;s existing livelihood strategies. V2 &amp; v3 Adjust budget.</narrative>
  </description>
